rvice/ndnp/mnhi/batch_mnhi_falstaff_ver01/data/sn86010115/00542864977/1937121601/0493.pdf", "segment_count": 8, "url": "https://www.loc.gov/resource/sn86010115/1937-12-16/ed-1/", "word_coordinates": "https://tile.loc.gov/text-services/word-coordinates-service"}], "segment_id": "/service/ndnp/mnhi/batch_mnhi_falstaff_ver01/data/sn86010115/00542864977/1937121601/0493.xml", "segments": [{"access_restricted": false, "aka": ["http://www.loc.gov/resource/sn86010115/1937-12-16/ed-1/?sp=8"], "batch": ["mnhi_falstaff_ver01"], "campaigns": [], "composite_location": ["0/united states/", "1/united states/minnesota/", "2/united states/minnesota/clearwater/", "3/united states/minnesota/clearwater/bagley/"], "contributor": ["minnesota historical society; saint paul, mn"], "date": "1937-12-16", "dates": ["1937-12-16"], "description": ["FME EIGHT Employment Law Effective in 1938 Continued from page 1 lief or charity Of course benefit checks cannot and will not be given unemployed workers for indefinite periods The rate and duration of benefits will depend upon each workers indi vidual earnings record for it is up on the earnings of workers that employers are contributing into the fund The maximum weekly bene fit rate will be sls The minimum will be approximately 6 The max imum duration of benefits will be 16 weeks in any one year The Minnesota State Employ ment Service which is free to work er and employer alike will operate on a statewide basis beginning on January 1 1938 It will have as its principal function the registration of unemployed workers and the seeking of jobs for them The ser vice which has absorbed the Na tional ReEmployment Service will operate in conjunction with the un employment compensation division both being divisions of the State In dustrial Commission State employment service offi cers will be located in cities and towns throughout the state where they can best serve the largest num ber of persons The offices will have a direct connection with the unemploymen